CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1964, pg. 1 reads:" World-Wide Delegation - The nearly 900 delegates attending the Methodist General Conference in Pittsburgh is world-wide, representing many races that inhabit the globe. The Courier cameraman captured some of these in above pictures...Second photo: Delegates from India (left to right): Rev. I.V. Naster, C.C. Naster and J.M .Contractor of India....-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Indian delegates, from left: Rev. I.V. Naster, C.C. Naster, and J.M .Contractor, posed in interior during 1964 United Methodist Church General Conference
